notes_fields.Macroscopic_Features: Small bright orange apothecia, first closed and goblet shaped then opening in maturity to cup shaped and then saucer shaped with a crenate (scalloped) margin; largest apothecia 8 mm in diameter; underside paler orange and covered with downy hairs, not so evident when the fungus is moist but easily visible as it begins to dry; stipe present or absent, usually buried in the substrate.
notes_fields.Microscopic_Features: Ellipsoid to cylindrical spores with a lateral depression, length (21.8) 22.7-25.0 (25.5) µm, width (12.1) 13.1-14.6 (15.0) µm, Q ratio (1.6) 1.6-1.8 (1.9); ornamented with a continuous, hyaline reticulum; spores contain a single large guttule that constitutes almost the entire spore volume; 8 spores per ascus, obliquely oriented and overlapping.
